08121nam a22010455i 9783110645880DE-B159720221201113901.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||221201t20192019gw     fo  d z      eng d  a97831106458807 a10.1515/97831106458802doi  a(DE-B1597)512687  a(OCoLC)1114885459  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  agwcDE 4aBL65.C62bR458 2019 7aPOL0030002bisacsh  aMS 6750qSEPA2rvk0(DE-625)rvk/123766:00aReligious Communities and Civil Society in Europe. nVolume I, pReligious Communities and Civil Society in Europe ; Analyses and Perspectives on a Complex Interplay, Volume I /ced. by Rupert Graf Strachwitz. 1aMünchen ;aWien : bDe Gruyter Oldenbourg, c[2019] 4c©2019  a1 online resource (400 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda0 aMaecenata Schriften ,x1866-122X ;v1500tFrontmatter -- tContent -- tForeword -- tIntroduction -- tFrom church diplomacy to civil society activism: the case of Bishop Irineos Galanakis in the framework of Greek German relations during the Cold War -- tIn the shadow of the ‘prevailing’ religion: religious communities and civil society in Greece -- tThe Orthodox Church of Greece and civic activism in the context of the financial crisis -- t“The Catholic Community and Civil Society in Italy” -- tReligion and civic engagement: European patterns and digging deeper in the Netherlands -- tReligiosity and civic engagement in latemodern Swedish society -- tA Diversity of Roles – The Actions Taken by Religious Communities in Sweden during the “Refugee Crisis” in 2015 -- tThe Islamic community in the secular state: its organisation, role, position, and functioning – a case study of Bosnia and Herzegovina -- tReport on Faith-Based Organisations and Civic Engagement in Europe -- tRelations Between the State and Religious Organisations in Europe From a Legal Perspective -- tBibliography -- tContributors0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aDerzeit wird die Frage nach der Rolle von Religionen im öffentlichen Raum häufig unter den Vorzeichen Gewalt, Fundamentalismus und Kulturkonflikt betrachtet. Eine andere Perspektive erhält hingegen sowohl in der öffentlichen Debatte als auch in sozialwissenschaftlichen Untersuchungen weitaus weniger Aufmerksamkeit: Wie steht es in Europa um das Verhältnis von Religionszugehörigen und Religionsgemeinschaften zu dem Teil des öffentlichen Raums, der als Zivilgesellschaft bezeichnet wird und der gerade in jüngster Zeit an Bedeutung gewonnen hat? In welchem Maße können und wollen sie über die rituelle Heilsvermittlung hinaus gesellschaftliche Partizipations-, Integrations-, Sozialisations- oder Interessenartikulationsfunktionen – und damit genuin zivilgesellschaftliche Aufgaben – übernehmen? Die Ausgangsfrage des dem vorliegenden Band zugrundeliegenden Forschungsprojekts lautete daher zunächst: Wie steht es um die Zuordnung der Religionsgemeinschaften? Sind sie, möglicherweise sogar unabhängig von ihrem Rechtsstatus, der Zivilgesellschaft neuer Definition zuzuordnen? Autorinnen und Autoren unterschiedlicher Disziplinen haben sich diesem Fragenkomplex in mehreren europäischen Ländern genähert. Fallstudien über Griechenland, Italien, Schweden und Bosnien-Herzegowina werden zudem ergänzt durch komparative religionsrechtliche Betrachtungen.  aThe seemingly vitalizing impact of religiosity on civil society is a research topic that has been extensively looked into, not only in the USA, but increasingly also in a European context. What is missing is an evaluation of the role of institutionalized religious communities, and of circumstances that facilitate or impede their status as civil society organisations. This anthology in two volumes aims at closing this gap by providing case studies regarding political, legal and historical aspects in various European countries. Vol. I provides an introduction and looks at cases in Greece, Italy, the Netherlands, Sweden, and Bosnia and Herzegovina, as well as chapters on legal issues and data, and comprehensive bibliography.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aReligion and civil societyzEurope. 0aReligion and statezEurope. 4aEuropa. 4aReligion. 4aReligionsgemeinschaft. 4aReligionspolitik. 4aZivilgesellschaft. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Civics & Citizenship.2bisacsh1 aBattaglia, Fabio, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDekker, Paul, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDimanopoulou, Pandora, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aD’Ambrosio, Rocco, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEssen, Johan von, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGraf Strachwitz, Rupert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGrosse, Julia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKessareas, Efstathios, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKulanić, Ahmed, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLundgren, Linnea, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMarkoviti, Margarita, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPloeg, Tymen J. van der, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aStrachwitz, Rupert Graf, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2019 Part 1z978311076246408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2019z978311071956708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishz978311061076508iTitle is part of eBook